You can change/set the connection time out 

**Spring Boot 1.4 and later**

As of Spring Boot 1.4 you can use the property server.connection-timeout. See Spring Boot&#39;s [common application properties][1].


  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/html/appendix-application-properties.html


**Spring Boot 1.3 and earlier**

Provide a customized EmbeddedServletContainerFactory bean:

    @Bean
    public EmbeddedServletContainerFactory servletContainerFactory() {
        TomcatEmbeddedServletContainerFactory factory = new TomcatEmbeddedServletContainerFactory();
    
